SIMPLE: eyeglass
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Eyeglass
<hw>Eye"glass`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>A lens
of glass worn in front of the eye to assist vision; -- usually used in
the plural, referring to a pair of lenses fixed together in a frame, and
worn resting on the bridge of the nose, to improve the vision. A single
eyeglass in a frame is called a <altname>monocle</altname>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source> <source>+PJC</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Eyepiece of a telescope, microscope, etc.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>The retina.</def> <mark>[Poetic]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>4.</sn> <def>A glass eyecup. See <er>Eyecup</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>eyeglasses</ent>⟦br⟧
